description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;County Durham and Darlington NHS Foundation Trust is one of the largest integrated care providers in England, serving a population of around 600,000 people. We are a high performing organisation with a track record of success. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for posts in Paediatrics (Non-Training) to support our current middle grade rota, for 24 - 36 months with possibility for extension. Applicants must have achieved competencies at ST3 level in Paediatrics or equivalent. Please ensure you meet essential criteria mentioned in job-description for shortlisting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts are suitable for applicants with an interest in acute paediatrics. The post holder will be based at Darlington Memorial Hospital, working on the middle grade rota covering Paediatric Ward and SCBU unit. He/she is also expected to help in outpatient clinics. Experience in Neonates and NLS is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a robust departmental teaching programme and you can access regional courses and conferences in North-East England. We support suitable doctors in their application for article 14.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust Doctors will join Trainees and APNP for on call work as part of the middle grade rota. There are 2 consultants are available for advice during the working weekdays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both sites have active Postgraduate Centers with a good library facility and are acknowledged for excellence in education. Single accommodation may be available&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For enquiries or to arrange a visit to the department, please contact&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
